## 5. Anti-candidates (excluded a priori, per Phase 0 §6)

Recorded here for closure so they are not proposed again:

- **σ1 on c2-style cancellation residue.** The Gate 3 case study. Fails criterion 2 by structural certainty (c2 lattice theorem in scope). See [`mcg_gate_3_killswitch/closeout.md`](../mcg_gate_3_killswitch/closeout.md).
- **Any magnitude residue of the form `round(V − f)` where V and f share a binade.** Same structural reason.
- **`|f_route_A − f_route_B|` (route divergence magnitude).** Subtracts two floats that are both BACL-mandated to be on lattices very close to each other; the difference is also on the lattice; integer-j subtraction collapses it. The j-symbol form (G-1) is the survivable reformulation.
- **Pure rounding-error magnitude `|f_float − f_exact|` after M-subtraction.** Magnitude alone; even if non-zero, it has no information content of the kind criterion 2 requires (G-1's reformulation as symbol-class is the right move).

